summary: guys friends at the table is criminally underrated... it's the best dang tabletop rpg podcast like... period and has great poc &...
body:
guys friends at the table is criminally underrated… it’s the best dang tabletop rpg podcast like… period and has great poc & LGBT rep in the cast as well as the characters

also it tells really epic stories, has incredible worldbuilding) and all the people on it are super creative and funny (especially the wonderful gm)

no offense to TAZ which I love but griffin even talks about how much he loves FATT and it still is unknown in comparison
